criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  2-60 years old, all genders;

          -  the first complete remission phase (CR1) of acute leukemia;

          -  planning to receive haplotype PBSCT;

          -  no uncontrolled current infections (new infections, body temperature still above 38 ℃
             after treatment with broad-spectrum antibiotics for 72h, except for other
             non-infectious factors);

          -  no organ failure.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  with poor compliance;

          -  with uncontrolled current infections；

          -  pregnancy;

          -  donors with contraindications of mobilization and collection of peripheral blood stem
             cells;

          -  with mental sickness
